ctroscopic data, N(1520), has a decay constant into the N\\pi\nchannel that is comparable with f_{NN\\pi}. This gives an independent\nexperimental verification of the chiral symmetry restoration scenario.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 22 Jun 2007 08:55:34 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 25 Sep 2007 17:25:16 GMT"}],"update_date":"2008-11-26"}
